President Obama spoke with Acting Ethiopian Prime Minister Hailemariam Desalegn and expressed his condolences on behalf of the American people for the loss experienced by Ethiopia. The President acknowledged the significant contributions made by former Prime Minister Meles to Ethiopia's development and regional peace and security. President Obama emphasized the United States' commitment to maintaining a partnership with Ethiopia and encouraged Acting Prime Minister Hailemariam to use his leadership to further support development, democracy, human rights, and regional security in Ethiopia.